  <mainDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    Rational Software Architect Web client supports the annotating and commenting of design artifacts through modern&#xD;
    implementations of web browser technology, without the need to install additional software onto the user's workstation.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    With the Web client you can:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Comment on design artifacts.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Graphically annotate design diagrams.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    &lt;b>Creating and updating text comments&lt;/b>&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    You can locate the design element that you want to comment on by:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Browsing in the Design Explorer.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Viewing a diagram.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Selecting &lt;b>Search for comments&lt;/b> or &lt;b>Search for elements with comments&lt;/b>.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Typing a query into the &lt;b>Search&lt;/b> window.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Once you have located the design element you want to comment on, click &lt;b>New Comment&lt;/b> or &lt;b>Reply to Comment&lt;/b>.&#xD;
    Each comment contains a subject and the text comment itself.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    If you are commenting about design elements shown in a diagram, you can add graphical annotations to support your&#xD;
    textual commentary.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    &lt;b>Adding graphical annotations to a diagram&lt;/b>&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Click &lt;b>New Comment&lt;/b>. The Design Manager graphical annotation tool palette is displayed:&lt;br />&#xD;
        Click &lt;b>Line&lt;/b> to draw a straight line.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Click &lt;b>Pencil&lt;/b> to draw a free-form line.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Click &lt;b>Text&lt;/b> to add text.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Click &lt;b>Oval&lt;/b>, &lt;b>Rectangle&lt;/b> or &lt;b>Cloud&lt;/b> to draw that kind of shape.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        After you have finished adding your annotations, click &lt;b>Save&lt;/b>.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    The same steps to comment or annotate design elements can be followed using the Rational Software Architect Client&#xD;
    Extension if the Eclipse plug-in has been installed on the Rational Software Architect desktop application.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    The following Rational Software Architect online help topic is useful to understand commenting capabilities: &lt;a&#xD;  
    href=&quot;http://publib.boulder.ibm.com/infocenter/rsahelp/v8/topic/com.ibm.dm.rsa.client.doc/topics/t_dm_rsa_marking_ov.html&quot;&#xD;
     target=&quot;_blank&quot;  >Marking and commenting on model elements&lt;/a>.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Resources to gain hands-on experience on design management features: &lt;a&#xD;  
    href=&quot;http://publib.boulder.ibm.com/infocenter/rdmhelp/v4/topic/com.ibm.dm.ispt.doc/topics/c_gs_essentials_of_dm.html&quot;&#xD;
    target=&quot;_blank&quot;  >Essentials of Design Management with Rational Software Architect&lt;/a>.&#xD;
&lt;/p></mainDescription>
